('Aberfeldy', 'Aberfeldy', 'https://www.aberfeldy-golfclub.co.uk/', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'highlands', '', 56.621756, -3.871285, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'e', 0xe61000000101000000bf0b5bb3954f4c407ff6234564f80ec0, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'Aberfeldy Golf Club is a charming, traditional Scottish golf course nestled in the scenic town of Aberfeldy, in the heart of Perthshire. Established in the early 20th century, the course combines parkland and moorland features, offering a blend of strategy and natural beauty that appeals to golfers of all abilities. Rolling fairways wind through mature trees, with subtle elevation changes providing both challenge and variety throughout the round.\r\n\r\nThe layout emphasizes precision over power, rewarding thoughtful shot placement and careful navigation of bunkers and natural hazards. Several holes feature views of the surrounding Highland hills and the nearby River Tay, creating a tranquil backdrop that enhances the golfing experience. The greens are well-maintained and subtly contoured, demanding a careful and confident putting stroke.\r\n\r\nAberfeldy Golf Club is known for its warm, welcoming atmosphere, reflecting the friendly spirit of the local community. While modest in length, the course\'s design challenges players with strategic choices and the occasional Highland breeze that can alter play. For visitors, it offers an authentic Scottish golfing experience, combining history, natural beauty, and enjoyable playability. Aberfeldy is a must-visit for anyone looking to enjoy a classic, scenic course away from the crowds of Scotland\'s more famous links.', ''),
