('anstruther', 'Anstruther', 'https://www.anstruthergolf.co.uk/home', 'https://www.anstruthergolf.co.uk/home', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'fife', '', 56.219150, -2.706010, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'c', 0xe6100000010100000012312592e8a505c08e75711b0d1c4c40, 'nonlinks', 'Yes', 'Anstruther Golf Club, situated on the Fife coast, is a classic links course that showcases the best of Scottish seaside golf. Its firm, undulating fairways and well-protected greens require precision and strategic thinking, while the coastal winds add an extra dimension to club selection and shot execution. The course balances challenge and playability, making it accessible to beginners while providing a satisfying test for experienced golfers.\r\n\r\nSeveral holes offer spectacular views of the North Sea, with dunes and native grasses creating natural hazards that enhance both the difficulty and visual appeal of the layout. The mixture of shorter par threes and longer holes encourages variety in shot-making and tactical decision-making.\r\n\r\nAnstruther Golf Club is celebrated for its friendly and welcoming atmosphere, reflecting the town\'s community spirit. Golfers visiting the course enjoy not only a competitive challenge but also the scenic beauty of Fife\'s coastline. Combining classic links design, strategic holes, and panoramic sea views, Anstruther Golf Club delivers a memorable and authentic Scottish golfing experience.', ''),
('arbroath', 'Arbroath', 'https://www.arbroathgolfcourse.co.uk/', 'https://www.arbroathgolfcourse.co.uk/', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'angus', '', 56.543390, -2.622560, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'c', 0xe610000001010000009a7cb3cd8d454c40d061bebc00fb04c0, 'links', 'Yes', 'Arbroath Golf Links is a traditional Scottish links course set along the rugged North Sea coastline, just outside the historic fishing town of Arbroath. Established in 1877, it is one of the older courses in the region and offers a classic out-and-back layout that makes full use of the natural dunes and coastal terrain. The course is relatively short by modern standards, but its defence lies in tight fairways, revetted bunkers, and the ever-present coastal wind, which can transform club selection and strategy from one hole to the next.\r\n\r\nFirm, fast-running fairways reward thoughtful positioning rather than raw power, while the subtly contoured greens demand a confident putting stroke. Several holes play directly along the shoreline, providing expansive views across the North Sea and adding a genuine sense of exposure to the elements. Accuracy off the tee is essential, as the gorse and rough can quickly punish wayward shots.\r\n\r\nArbroath is widely regarded as a friendly and welcoming club, with a relaxed atmosphere that reflects its community roots. It offers an authentic links experience without the formality or cost associated with some of Scotland\'s championship venues, making it popular with both visitors and local golfers. For players seeking traditional seaside golf, strategic shot-making, and a true test of links conditions, Arbroath Golf Links provides a memorable and thoroughly enjoyable round.', ''),
