('leslie', 'Leslie', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/leslie#/course/1', '', 'Yes', 'No', 'brs', '', '', 'fife', 'Yes', 56.205103, -3.213206, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'leslie', 1, 0, 'e', 0xe61000000101000000e17cea58a5b409c0dfa7aad0401a4c40, 'nonlinks', 'No', '', ''),
('levenlinks', 'Leven', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/levenlinks', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/levenlinks#/course/1', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'brs', 'brs', '', 'fife', 'Yes', 56.197846, -2.988865, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'levenlinks', 1, 1, 'b', 0xe61000000101000000b745990d32e907c07cd2890453194c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'Leven Links is a giant of the Scottish game and one of the oldest and purest links courses in the world. Originally founded in 1846, the course took its modern 18-hole form in 1868 following input from Old Tom Morris. To celebrate its opening, an exhibition match was held and won by the 17-year-old Young Tom Morris, the greatest player of his era. It is a classic links characterized by ancient sand dunes, deep pot bunkers, and the famous \"Scoonie Burn\" that guards the final green.\r\n\r\nThe course has an immense tournament pedigree, having served as a Final Qualifying venue for the Open Championship on six occasions between 1978 and 2005. It remains a regular host for the Standard Life Leven Gold Medal, the world\'s oldest amateur stroke-play tournament. Leven is a \"thinking man\'s links\" where the bump-and-run shot is an essential tool, especially during the dry summer months. Shared between the Leven Thistle Golf Club and the Leven Golfing Society, the course represents the absolute pinnacle of traditional Fife links golf, offering a historic and uncompromising test of skill.', ''),
