('longniddry', 'Longniddry', 'https://www.longniddrygolfclub.co.uk/visitorbooking/', 'competition2', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'intelligent', 'intelligent', '', 'eastlothian', 'Yes', 55.976589, -2.908344, 0, 0, '', 'https://www.longniddrygolfclub.co.uk', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'c', 0xe610000001010000008124ecdb494407c011514cde00fd4b40, 'links', 'No', 'Longniddry Golf Club is a unique and prestigious course on the East Lothian \"Golf Coast.\" Founded in 1921, it was designed by the esteemed Harry Colt, one of the most famous architects in the history of the game. Longniddry is a rare hybrid, blending the characteristics of a traditional links with the shelter and trees of a woodland course. It famously has no par-fives, meaning its par of 68 is one of the toughest to beat in the country. It has frequently served as an Open Championship Qualifying venue.\r\n\r\nThe course has a high-society pedigree and has counted many prominent figures from Edinburgh\'s legal and medical circles among its members. Notable visitors have included Sir Henry Cotton, who praised the strategic demands of Colt\'s design. The layout is notorious for its sea breezes and its fast, undulating greens. Because there are no par-fives, accuracy and a sharp short game are absolutely paramount. Longniddry offers a refined, aristocratic experience that bridges the gap between the wild links of Gullane and the manicured parklands of Edinburgh, making it an essential stop for the serious golfer.', ''),
