('lumphanangolfclub', 'Lumphanan', 'https://www.lumphanangolfclub.co.uk/Teebooking/SearchSlots.aspx', 'https://www.lumphanangolfclub.co.uk/Teebooking/SearchSlots.aspx', 'Yes', 'No', 'dotgolf', 'dotgolf', '', 'aberdeen', 'Yes', 57.126173, -2.682287, 0, 2422, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'e', 0xe610000001010000003be3fbe2527505c0b151d66f26904c40, 'nonlinks', 'No', '', ''),
('lundingc', 'Lundin Links', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/lundingc#/course/1', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/lundingc#/course/1', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'brs', 'brs', '', 'fife', 'Yes', 56.216630, -2.949101, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'lundingc', 1, 1, 'b', 0xe61000000101000000a3cedc43c29707c08faa2688ba1b4c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'Lundin Links is a powerhouse of Scottish golf and a perennial Final Qualifying venue for the Open Championship. Originally founded in 1868, the course was redesigned in 1909 by the legendary James Braid after the club split with its neighbor, Leven. Braid utilized the dramatic, undulating links land and the adjacent higher ground to create a hybrid masterpiece. The first five holes are pure links, the middle section offers a more elevated \"parkland\" feel with spectacular views over the Firth of Forth, and the finishing stretch returns to the classic dunes.\r\n\r\nThe club has hosted almost every major amateur championship in Scotland and has seen legends like Gene Sarazen and Gary Player grace its fairways. Notable for its narrow fairways, deep bunkers, and the \"Miles Burn\" that crosses the course twice, it is a formidable test of accuracy and nerve. The clubhouse is an architectural gem, and the sense of history is palpable. Lundin Links is a \"pure\" golfer\'s course-historic, challenging, and impeccably maintained-offering one of the most varied and rewarding links experiences in Fife.', ''),
