('Lynedoch', 'Murrayshall - Lynedoch', 'https://www.murrayshall.co.uk/golf/', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'perthshire', '', 56.419170, -3.368315, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'e', 0xe610000001010000008a027d224ff20ac06fbbd05ca7354c40, 'nonlinks', 'No', '', ''),
('machrie', 'The Machrie', 'https://book.rguest.eu/onecart/golf/courses/10278/TheMachrie', 'https://book.rguest.eu/onecart/golf/courses/10278/TheMachrie', 'Yes', 'No', '', '', 'mon,tue,wed,thu,fri,sat,sun', 'islands', 'No', 55.664637, -6.256074, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'b', 0xe61000000101000000726c3d43380619c0145b41d312d54b40, 'links', 'Yes', 'The Machrie, located on the Isle of Islay, is a legendary links that sits among the upper echelons of world golf. Originally designed in 1891 by Willie Campbell, the course underwent a total transformation in 2018 by architect David J. Russell. The redesign modernized the layout while preserving the soul of its ancient, towering dunes. It is a pure links experience, characterized by massive elevation changes, hidden hollows, and panoramic views of the Atlantic Ocean and the Big Strand beach.\r\n\r\nThe course has a storied history, once hosting an exhibition match in 1901 with a prize fund that rivaled the Open Championship. Notable visitors include every serious student of links golf, drawn by its reputation for raw beauty and tactical complexity. The turf is firm and fast-running, and the wind is a constant, shifting factor. The modern hotel and clubhouse have turned The Machrie into a world-class destination. To play here is to experience golf in its most elemental form-a wild, spectacular, and deeply moving journey across one of the most historic pieces of links land in existence.', ''),
('machriebay', 'Machrie Bay', 'https://www.machriebay.com/Teebooking/SearchSlots.aspx', 'https://www.machriebay.com/Teebooking/SearchSlots.aspx', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'dotgolf', 'dotgolf', '', 'islands', 'Yes', 55.555053, -5.341588, 0, 2428, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'e', 0xe61000000101000000fed2a23ec95d15c0fa4509fa0bc74b40, 'nonlinks', 'No', '', ''),
('machrihanish', 'Machrihanish', 'https://machrihanish.hub.clubv1.com/Visitors/TeeSheet', 'https://machrihanish.hub.clubv1.com/Visitors/TeeSheet', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'clubv1', 'clubv1', '', 'islands', 'Yes', 55.433016, -5.716739, 0, 0, '', '', 'machrihanish', 7910, '', 0, 1, 'b', 0xe610000001010000002b1213d4f0dd16c087527b116db74b40, 'links', 'Yes', 'Machrihanish Golf Club is a titan of the game, home to what is widely considered the greatest opening hole in world golf. Designed by the \"Grand Old Man of Golf\" Old Tom Morris, in 1876, the course is a pure links situated on the remote Kintyre Peninsula. The 1st hole, \"Battery\" requires a heroic drive over the Atlantic beach to find the fairway-a shot that has challenged every great player from Babe Zaharias to Jack Nicklaus. It is an uncompromising and atmospheric test of links golf.\r\n\r\nThe course is a sanctuary of natural dunes, hidden hollows, and lightning-fast greens. It has a prestigious tournament history, frequently hosting the Scottish Ladies\' Championship and regional qualifying for major events. Notable for its \"out and back\" routing, the course takes players deep into the wild dunes of Machrihanish Bay. The sense of isolation and the raw power of the sea make playing here a spiritual experience for many. It is a course that rewards creativity and a low ball flight. For any serious golfer, a trip to Machrihanish is a pilgrimage to one of the most hallowed and beautiful sites in the history of the sport.', ''),
('machrihanishdunes', 'Machrihanish Dunes', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/machrihanishdunes', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/machrihanishdunes#/course/1', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'brs', 'brs', '', 'islands', 'Yes', 55.451633, -5.710137, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'machrihanishdunes', 1, 1, 'b', 0xe61000000101000000dcb75a272ed716c0ae65321ccfb94b40, 'links', 'Yes', 'Machrihanish Dunes is a revolutionary modern links that sits adjacent to the historic Old Tom Morris course. Opened in 2009 and designed by David McLay Kidd (the architect behind Bandon Dunes), it is the first course ever built on a site of Special Scientific Interest (SSSI). As such, the design was \"found\" rather than built; no heavy machinery was used to shape the fairways, and the layout follows the natural, rugged contours of the dunes exactly as they have sat for centuries.\r\n\r\nThe course is a wild, adventurous experience, featuring massive, undulating greens and deep natural blow-outs. It is notoriously difficult, especially when the wind whips off the Atlantic, requiring a huge variety of shots and a high degree of patience. Notable visitors include modern stars of the game who appreciate the \"raw\" and ecological approach to design. The Dunes offers a fascinating contrast to its neighbor, providing a much more rugged and unpredictable round. It is a testament to sustainable design and a \"must-play\" for those who want to see how the origins of links golf are being reimagined for the 21st century.', ''),
