('murcarlinks', 'Murcar', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/murcarlinks', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/murcarlinks#/course/1', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'brs', 'brs', '', 'aberdeen', 'Yes', 57.206424, -2.068247, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'murcarlinks', 1, 1, 'b', 0xe61000000101000000a1664815c58b00c0048e041a6c9a4c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'Murcar Links is a world-class championship course that sits adjacent to the famous Royal Aberdeen links. Established in 1909 and designed by Archie Simpson, it was later refined by James Braid. It is a rugged, spectacular links characterized by massive sand dunes, deep hollows, and blind shots. Murcar has a significant tournament pedigree, having hosted the European Tour\'s Saltire Energy Paul Lawrie Matchplay and the Scottish Challenge Tour.\r\n\r\nThe course is famously difficult, especially when the North Sea gales blow across the exposed dunes. Notable members have included many of the North East\'s top amateurs. The signature 7th hole, \"Serpentine\" is a par-four that requires a nerve-wracking drive between towering dunes to a narrowing fairway. Murcar is a \"pure\" links in every sense-raw, uncompromising, and visually stunning. It offers a more rugged and wild experience than some of its more manicured neighbors, making it a favorite for those who want to experience the true, untamed nature of Scottish coastal golf.', ''),
