('nairndunbargolf', 'Nairn Dunbar', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/nairndunbargolf#/course/1', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/nairndunbargolf#/course/1', 'Yes', 'No', 'brs', 'brs', '', 'highlands', 'Yes', 57.586222, -3.859008, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'nairndunbargolf', 1, 1, 'c', 0xe61000000101000000da0418963fdf0ec00d198f5209cb4c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'Nairn Dunbar Golf Links is a heavyweight of Northern golf, frequently overshadowed by its neighbor but a formidable championship test in its own right. Founded in 1899, the course has evolved into a rugged links-heathland hybrid. In recent years, a major restoration project returned the course to its \"pure\" links roots by removing gorse to reveal natural sand dunes. It has a high tournament pedigree, having hosted the British Amateur Championship and the Scottish Boys\' Championship.\r\n\r\nThe course is famous for its brutal opening stretch and its remarkably fast, true greens. Notable members have included several Walker Cup players, and the club prides itself on a competitive yet welcoming environment. Unlike some traditional links, Nairn Dunbar offers a variety of holes that wind through both dunes and more sheltered, tree-lined areas. The wind off the Moray Firth is a constant defender of par, making a low-ball flight essential. It is a polished, professional club that offers a world-class links experience with a slightly more modern and relaxed feel than the ancient coastal giants.', ''),
('nairngc', 'Nairn', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/nairngc#/course/1', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/nairngc#/course/1', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'brs', 'brs', '', 'highlands', 'Yes', 57.585206, -3.909676, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'nairngc', 1, 1, 'b', 0xe6100000010100000016a6ef3504470fc024b6bb07e8ca4c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'The Nairn Golf Club is a global masterpiece and a jewel of the Moray Firth. Established in 1887 and refined by legends including Old Tom Morris, James Braid, and Ben Sayers, it is a pure links of the highest order. It is one of the few courses in the world where the sea is visible from every single hole. Nairn has an immense international reputation, famously hosting the 1999 Walker Cup and the 2012 Curtis Cup, where the quality of its firm, fast fairways drew worldwide acclaim.\r\n\r\nThe course is renowned for having some of the best greens in Scotland-lightning-fast and remarkably smooth. Famous members and visitors include royalty and major champions who seek out its technical complexity. The first seven holes hug the shoreline so closely that a stray hook will literally land in the North Sea. It is a traditional, aristocratic club where the standards of play and etiquette are held in the highest regard. To play Nairn is to experience the absolute pinnacle of links architecture-a beautiful, unforgiving, and spiritually uplifting journey across the Highland coastline.', ''),
