('newburghonythan', 'Newburgh on Ythan', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/newburghonythan#/course/1', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/newburghonythan#/course/1', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'brs', 'brs', '', 'aberdeen', 'Yes', 57.313270, -2.001010, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'newburghonythan', 1, 1, 'c', 0xe610000001010000004da3c9c5189806c002bc051214974b40, 'links', 'Yes', 'Newburgh on Ythan Golf Club is a spectacular links course situated at the mouth of the River Ythan in Aberdeenshire. Originally a 9-hole course founded in 1888, it was extended to a full 18 holes in the 1990s. The course is a \"tale of two halves\": the front nine offers a more modern, hilly links feel with expansive views, while the back nine winds through massive, ancient dunes that are among the most dramatic in the country. It sits adjacent to the Forvie National Nature Reserve, making it a haven for wildlife.\r\n\r\nThe course is famous for its demanding elevation changes and the blind shots required through the dunes. While it lacks a \"celebrity\" architect, the natural routing is a masterclass in links design. Notable for its firm turf and punishing rough, Newburgh is a favorite for those who enjoy the \"raw\" and unadulterated side of links golf. The views from the 4th tee, overlooking the estuary and the North Sea, are worth the green fee alone. It is a welcoming, community-led club that offers a wild and memorable challenge that rivals the more famous links of the North East.', ''),
('newcastleton', 'Newcastleton', 'https://www.visitnewcastleton.com/things-to-do-in-newcastleton/golf/', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'south', '', 55.180300, -2.824266, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'e', 0xe610000001010000004da3c9c5189806c002bc051214974b40, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'Newcastleton Golf Club is a rugged and charming 9-hole moorland course situated in the heart of the Liddesdale Valley in the Scottish Borders. Established in 1910, the course is perched on the slopes of Holm Hill, offering panoramic views over the village and the surrounding border hills. It is a \"natural\" course in the truest sense, where the fairways follow the steep contours of the land and the primary hazards are provided by the heather, gorse, and the local topography.\r\n\r\nThe club is an \"honesty box\" facility, maintained with immense pride by a small group of local volunteers. While it doesn\'t host professional tournaments, it is a beloved part of the local community and offers a peaceful, solitary experience for visiting golfers. The layout requires a good level of fitness due to the steep climbs, but the reward is a series of exhilarating elevated tee shots. Newcastleton is a place where you can escape the pressures of modern life and experience the game as it was played over a century ago-simple, beautiful, and deeply connected to the landscape.', ''),
