('northberwick', 'North Berwick', 'https://www.northberwickgolfclub.com/tee_booking_request_form', 'https://www.northberwickgolfclub.com/tee_booking_request_form', 'No', 'No', '', '', 'mon,tue,wed,thu,sun', 'eastlothian', '', 56.056085, -2.727239, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'a', 0xe6100000010100000086014bae62d105c0e96514cb2d074c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'The West Links at North Berwick is a global icon and a masterpiece of traditional links design. Founded in 1832, the course is a pure links that starts and finishes in the heart of the town. It is home to some of the most copied holes in the world, most notably the 15th, \"Redan\" which has been replicated on nearly every continent. Unlike many modern courses, North Berwick is famous for its quirks-including stone walls that must be lofted over and ancient, deep-seated bunkers.\r\n\r\nThe club has hosted every major amateur event and served as a Final Qualifying venue for the Open Championship for decades. Notable members have included legends of the game and icons of the Scottish establishment. The 13th hole, \"Pit\" requires an approach over a historic stone wall to a green nestled on the other side. North Berwick is a \"fun\" links in the truest sense; it is a creative, unpredictable, and spiritually uplifting journey along the Firth of Forth. To play here is to experience the very soul of Scottish golf architecture.', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/QED9z5mRzEI?si=JGvKhbP-xGLN85Gb'),
