('prestwickstnicholas', 'Prestwick St Nicholas', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/prestwickstnicholas', '', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'brs', 'clubv1', '', 'ayrshire', 'Yes', 55.493280, -4.620230, 0, 0, '', '', '', 175, 'prestwickstnicholas', 1, 1, 'c', 0xe6100000010100000009feb7921d7b12c0ace28dcc23bf4b40, 'links', 'No', 'Prestwick St Nicholas is a historic and scenic links course located just south of the famous Open venue. Founded in 1851, the club is the 26th oldest in the world, and Old Tom Morris himself was a founding member and a frequent competitor on these fairways. The course is a traditional \"out and back\" links that hugs the shoreline of the Firth of Clyde, offering stunning views across to the Isle of Arran and the Ailsa Craig.\r\n\r\nThe layout is characterized by its firm turf, deep bunkers, and the \"Quarry\" holes that provide a unique and challenging middle section. Notable for its fast greens and its exposure to the sea breezes, St Nicholas is a regular host for the Scottish Ladies\' Championship and national senior events. It is a refined and welcoming club that maintains a strong sense of its 19th-century heritage. For those seeking an authentic links experience with deep historical ties to the founders of the professional game, St Nicholas is an essential and rewarding stop.', ''),
