('roxburghe', 'Roxburghe', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/roxburghe#/course/1', 'https://visitors.brsgolf.com/roxburghe#/course/1', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'brs', 'brs', '', 'borders', 'Yes', 55.558350, -2.470770, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'roxburghe', 1, 1, 'e', 0xe61000000101000000dc80cf0f23c403c05ddc460378c74b40, 'nonlinks', 'No', '', ''),
('royalaberdeen', 'Royal Aberdeen', 'https://www.royalaberdeengolf.com/', '', 'No', 'Yes', '', 'clubv1', '', 'aberdeen', 'No', 57.186261, -2.077226, 0, 0, '', '', '', 191, '', 0, 1, 'a', 0xe61000000101000000093543aa289e00c098c28366d7974c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'Founded in 1780, Royal Aberdeen is the sixth oldest golf club in the world. The Balgownie Links is a legendary championship venue, originally designed by the Simpson brothers and later refined by James Braid. It is widely regarded as having one of the finest front nines in golf, as the holes weave through massive, ancient dunes that offer total protection from the wind. The back nine moves onto higher ground, providing a more traditional, exposed links challenge with panoramic North Sea views.\r\n\r\nThe club hosted the 2014 Scottish Open (won by Justin Rose) and the 2011 Walker Cup. Notable members have historically included the elite of Aberdeen\'s professional classes. The signature 8th hole, \"Shelter\" is a par-three surrounded by ten bunkers. It is a traditional, prestigious club where the standards of etiquette are as high as the quality of the turf. To play Balgownie is to experience the very essence of traditional Scottish links golf-rugged, historic, and strategically brilliant.', ''),
('royalaberdeensilverburn', 'Royal Aberdeen - Silverburn', 'https://www.royalaberdeengolf.com/', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'aberdeen', '', 57.178504, -2.083118, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'e', 0xe61000000101000000e2ab1dc539aa00c0431a1538d9964c40, 'links', 'No', '', ''),
('royaldornoch', 'Royal Dornoch', 'https://booking.royaldornoch.com/', 'https://booking.royaldornoch.com/', 'No', 'No', '', '', 'mon,tue,wed,thu,fri,sun', 'highlands', 'No', 57.887779, -4.013768, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'a', 0xe61000000101000000e1ecd632190e10c0ad8905bea2f14c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'Royal Dornoch\'s Championship Course is frequently ranked among the top five golf courses in the world. Golf has been played here since 1616, making it one of the oldest sites in the game. Old Tom Morris extended the course to 18 holes in 1886. It is the spiritual home of the legendary architect Donald Ross, who was born in Dornoch and served as the club\'s professional before moving to America to design Pinehurst No. 2. Many of Ross\'s design hallmarks-most notably the inverted-saucer greens-originated here.\r\n\r\nThe course is a natural masterpiece, winding along the Dornoch Firth with elevated tees and raised greens that require surgical precision. It has hosted the British Amateur and is a site of pilgrimage for legends like Tom Watson, who famously called it the most fun he\'d ever had on a golf course. With its iconic yellow gorse and white-sand beaches, Dornoch offers a pure, \"timeless\" golfing experience. The club recently opened a magnificent new clubhouse in 2025, ensuring that its off-course facilities now match its world-class fairways.', ''),
