('royaltroon', 'Royal Troon - Old', 'https://www.brsgolf.com/royaltroon/visitor_home.php', '', 'Yes', 'No', 'brs', '', '', 'ayrshire', 'Yes', 55.532870, -4.649940, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 'royaltroon', 1, 1, 'a', 0xe61000000101000000ef7211df899912c080828b1535c44b40, 'links', 'No', 'Royal Troon\'s Old Course is one of the pillars of the Open Championship rotation, having hosted the tournament ten times (most recently in 2024). Designed by Willie Fernie in 1878 and refined by James Braid, it is a traditional \"out and back\" links. The front nine runs south along the coast, offering scoring opportunities, while the back nine turns into the prevailing wind and is widely considered the toughest finishing stretch in championship golf.\r\n\r\nThe course is home to two of the most famous holes in the world: the 8th, \"The Postage Stamp\" the shortest hole in Open golf, and the 11th, \"The Railway\" bordered by the Glasgow-Ayr train line. Legendary moments here include the 2016 \"Duel at Troon\" between Henrik Stenson and Phil Mickelson. Notable members have included giants of Scottish industry and sport. To play Troon is to experience a cathedral of the game-a stern, fair, and profoundly historic links that demands the absolute best from every part of your game.', ''),
