('scotscraiggolfclub', 'Scotscraig', 'https://www.scotscraiggolfclub.com/visitorbooking/', 'competition2', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'intelligent', 'intelligent', '', 'fife', 'Yes', 56.438607, -2.875595, 0, 0, '', 'https://www.scotscraiggolfclub.com', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'c', 0xe6100000010100000037548cf3370107c0f965304624384c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'Scotscraig Golf Club is a world-class championship venue and the 13th oldest golf club in the world, founded in 1817 by members of the St Andrews Society of Golfers. The layout is a unique \"links-heathland\" hybrid, featuring the firm turf of a links course but with gorse and heather-lined fairways more typical of an inland track. Designed by the \"Grand Masters\" Old Tom Morris and James Braid, it has served as a Final Qualifying venue for the Open Championship for decades.\r\n\r\nThe course is legendary for its small, firm greens and its demanding strategic layout. Notable players who have tackled Scotscraig during Open qualifying include Justin Rose, Ernie Els, and Lee Westwood. It is a prestigious, traditional club where the standards of play and maintenance are among the highest in Scotland. To play Scotscraig is to experience a masterclass in golf architecture; it is an unforgiving, historic, and beautifully presented test of the game that remains a mandatory stop for any serious golfer visiting Fife.', ''),
