('standrewsbalgove', 'St Andrews - Balgove', 'https://standrews.com/homepage', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'fife', '', 56.343684, -2.802423, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'e', 0xe610000001010000003677f4bf5c6b06c049145ad6fd2b4c40, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'The Balgove Course at St Andrews is the only 9-hole course at the \"Home of Golf\" specifically designed to cater to beginners, juniors, and families. While it sits in the shadow of the world-famous Old Course, the Balgove is maintained to the same exacting standards as the rest of the St Andrews Links Trust estate. It features wide fairways and large bunkers, providing a gentle introduction to the unique challenges of links golf.\r\n\r\nThe course is a vital part of the St Andrews community, serving as the primary training ground for the next generation of local golfers. It offers a relaxed and unpretentious environment where the pressure of the championship courses is absent. Notable for its accessibility and its perfectly manicured turf, the Balgove allows players to experience the \"magic\" of St Andrews without the daunting difficulty of the larger tracks. It is the perfect venue for a fun, stress-free \"nine\" in the heart of the world\'s most famous golfing town, proving that golf for all is a core value of the Links Trust.', ''),
('standrewscastle', 'St Andrews - Castle', 'https://standrews.com/homepage', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'fife', '', 56.343684, -2.802423, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'b', 0xe610000001010000003677f4bf5c6b06c049145ad6fd2b4c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'The Castle Course is the newest addition to the St Andrews Links Trust, opened in 2008 and designed by David McLay Kidd (the architect of Bandon Dunes). Perched on a rugged cliff-top overlooking the town, it offers a starkly different experience from the traditional links below. It is famous for its massive, rolling undulations and some of the most complex greens in the country. The layout is a visual masterpiece, with the North Sea visible from every hole and the skyline of St Andrews providing a dramatic backdrop.\r\n\r\nThe course has hosted the European Tour\'s St Andrews Bay Championship and is a favorite for those seeking a \"modern-traditional\" challenge. Notable for its 17th hole, a par-three requiring a heroic carry over a yawning chasm of sea and rock, it is a course that demands imagination and a steady nerve. While controversial when it first opened due to its difficulty, it has matured into a prestigious and exhilarating round that provides a thrilling, elevated contrast to the classic seaside tracks of the Auld Grey Toon.', ''),
('standrewsCraigtoun', 'St Andrews - Craigtoun', 'https://standrews.com/homepage', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'fife', '', 56.343684, -2.802423, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'c', 0xe610000001010000003677f4bf5c6b06c049145ad6fd2b4c40, 'links', 'No', 'The Craigtoun Course, located on the high ground overlooking St Andrews, is the only parkland layout in the town. Originally designed by Peter Thomson (five-time Open winner) and later significantly revised by Tim Liddy in 2006, the course offers a \"resort-style\" experience of the highest caliber. It is characterized by its wide-open spaces, rugged bunkering, and a \"heathland\" feel that provides a beautiful alternative to the coastal links.\r\n\r\nOwned by the Old Course Hotel, The Craigtoun has hosted the European Amateur Championship and is a regular venue for elite international events. Notable for its expansive views of the town and the sea, it is a \"big\" course that rewards powerful driving and strategic approach play. The greens are large and fast, and the gorse-lined fairways provide a colorful Highland-edge atmosphere. It is a polished, professional, and tranquil sanctuary that offers a world-class inland round in the world\'s most famous golfing destination.', ''),
('standrewseden', 'St Andrews - Eden', 'https://standrews.com/homepage', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'fife', '', 56.343684, -2.802423, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'c', 0xe610000001010000003677f4bf5c6b06c049145ad6fd2b4c40, 'links', 'No', 'The Eden Course was opened in 1914 to ease the pressure on the Old and New courses, designed by the legendary Harry Colt. Colt brought his signature strategic bunkering to the links, creating a layout that is shorter than its neighbors but arguably more technical. It is characterized by its small, well-guarded greens and several significant water hazards, including the Eden Estuary which comes into play on the early holes.\r\n\r\nThe club has a vibrant social scene and is a favorite for local medals and visiting societies. Notable for its \"traditional links\" feel without the intimidating length of a championship track, the Eden requires a high degree of accuracy off the tee. It has hosted various Scottish regional tournaments and remains a vital part of the St Andrews Links Trust estate. It is the perfect course for the \"thinking\" golfer who appreciates the subtleties of Colt\'s design and wants to experience the magic of St Andrews in a slightly more relaxed environment.', ''),
('standrewsjubilee', 'St Andrews - Jubilee', 'https://standrews.com/homepage', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'fife', '', 56.343684, -2.802423, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'b', 0xe610000001010000003677f4bf5c6b06c049145ad6fd2b4c40, 'links', 'No', 'The Jubilee Course is often cited by locals as the most difficult of all the St Andrews links. Originally opened in 1897 to commemorate Queen Victoria\'s Diamond Jubilee, it was a 12-hole course before being extended and eventually redesigned in 1988 by Donald Steel into a championship-standard links. It is situated on the narrowest strip of land between the New Course and the sea, featuring deep dunes and narrow fairways.\r\n\r\nThe course has hosted numerous amateur championships and is a regular test for the St Andrews Links Trophy. Notable for its relentless demand for accuracy, especially when the wind whips off the West Sands, the Jubilee provides a \"pure\" links experience that many believe is a truer test of skill than its more famous neighbors. The elevated tees offer stunning views of the estuary and the town. It is a rugged, uncompromising, and beautifully maintained track that represents the very best of modern links architecture in a historic setting.', ''),
('standrewsnew', 'St Andrews - New', 'https://standrews.com/homepage', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'fife', '', 56.343684, -2.802423, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'b', 0xe610000001010000003677f4bf5c6b06c049145ad6fd2b4c40, 'links', 'No', 'The New Course at St Andrews is only \"new\" in name-it was actually opened in 1895. Designed by the \"Grand Old Man of Golf\" Old Tom Morris, it was built to accommodate the increasing demand for golf in the town. It is a classic \"out and back\" links, running parallel to the Old Course, and many purists consider it a more consistent and \"fairer\" test than its more famous sibling. It features traditional gorse-lined fairways, deep bunkers, and fast-running turf.\r\n\r\nThe club has a prestigious history and shares many of the same views and conditions as the Old Course. Notable for its shared fairways and challenging finishing holes, the New Course is a regular venue for national amateur events. It is a favorite for local members who appreciate the logical flow of Old Tom\'s design. To play the New is to experience the absolute peak of late 19th-century links architecture-it is honest, challenging, and steeped in the traditions of the St Andrews Links Trust.', ''),
('standrewsold', 'St Andrews - Old', 'https://standrews.com/homepage', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'fife', '', 56.343684, -2.802423, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'a', 0xe610000001010000003677f4bf5c6b06c049145ad6fd2b4c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'The Old Course is the undisputed home of golf, the place where the game was born and where every great champion has walked. Its history stretches back over 600 years. Originally a natural progression across the links land, it was refined by Old Tom Morris and Alister MacKenzie. It is home to the most iconic landmarks in the sport: the Swilcan Bridge, the Road Hole (17th), and the massive double greens that span half an acre.\r\n\r\nMuirfield may be the most \"perfect\" design, but the Old Course is the most \"magical.\" It has hosted The Open Championship 30 times, with winners including Tiger Woods, Jack Nicklaus, and Bobby Jones. Notable members include the entire history of the R&A. To play here is a spiritual experience; the sense of history is palpable as you stand on the 1st tee. It is a public course that belongs to the world, offering a unique, strategic, and profoundly moving round of golf that every player dreams of completing once in their lifetime.', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/rrFpmSEUyHw?si=vpca-pUpebzkgo7p'),
('standrewsStrathtyrum', 'St Andrews - Strathtyrum', 'https://standrews.com/homepage', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'fife', '', 56.343684, -2.802423, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, 'e', 0xe610000001010000003677f4bf5c6b06c049145ad6fd2b4c40, 'nonlinks', 'No', 'The Strathtyrum Course was opened in 1993 to provide a more accessible and enjoyable links experience for players of all levels. While it is the shortest of the 18-hole courses at St Andrews, it is maintained to the same high standards as the championship tracks. Designed by Donald Steel, the layout features wider fairways and fewer bunkers, making it an ideal choice for a relaxed round or for those looking to build their confidence on links turf.\r\n\r\nThe course is particularly popular with families, seniors, and visitors who want to enjoy the St Andrews atmosphere without the brutal challenge of the Jubilee or the Old. Notable for its large, undulating greens that still require a sharp putting stroke, the Strathtyrum offers a scenic and tranquil environment. It provides a vital balance to the Links Trust\'s portfolio, ensuring that the \"Home of Golf\" remains a destination for everyone. It is a high-quality, friendly, and beautifully presented course that captures the joy of the game in its purest form.', ''),
