('TheRenaissanceClub', 'Renaissance', 'https://trcaa.com/', '', 'No', 'No', '', '', '', 'eastlothian', '', 56.051427, -2.811122, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, '', 0, 1, 'b', 0xe610000001010000006687f8872d7d06c0d190f12895064c40, 'links', 'Yes', 'The Renaissance Club in East Lothian is one of the most prestigious modern additions to the \"Home of Golf.\" Established in 2008 and designed by the acclaimed Tom Doak, it is a world-class links that blends contemporary luxury with traditional architectural values. Since 2019, the club has been the permanent home of the Scottish Open, hosting the world\'s best players, including Rory McIlroy and Xander Schauffele.\r\n\r\nThe course is a tactical masterpiece, featuring Doak\'s signature large, undulating greens and strategic bunkering that utilizes the natural landscape. The \"cliff-edge\" stretch (holes 9 through 11) offers breathtaking views of the Firth of Forth. Notable for its exclusive atmosphere and its \"Tour-standard\" conditioning, The Renaissance Club represents the pinnacle of modern Scottish golf. While it is a private club, it offers limited visitor access, providing a rare opportunity to play a course that has become a cornerstone of the professional international circuit.', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/Ud3ilD08u0w?si=05SFz8ZZa9EIASAA'),
